creator: Ernest Dowson
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 11 recordings of My Lady April by Ernest Dowson. This was the Weekly Poetry project for April 3, 2016. Read in English by Algy Pug; Bruce Kachuk; Bridget Herbes; Brian Darby; David Lawrence; Newgatenovelist; Greg Giordano; Ian King; Jennifer Fournier; Lee Ann Howlett and Twinkle. Ernest Christopher Dowson was an English poet, novelist, and short-story writer, often associated with the Decadent movement. ( Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B Audiobook (6MB)
subject: librivox; audiobooks;poetry; nature; spring; April; literature
